gene_name_short: preferably short identifier of the gene/part
gene_name_long: longer identifier that provides more information about the gene/part
product: The name of the larger gene collection within which the part is contained
plasmid_name: a semiformal name by which to identify the plasmid (preferably unique, but doesn't have to be)
backbone: the vector backbone that the part is put into
sequencing_primer_forward: forward primers for sequencing (in the plasmid)
sequencing_primer_reverse: reverse primers for sequencing (in the plasmid)
genbank_source_id: ID of gene in the plasmid
genbank_source_link: actual link to the gene in the plasmid
genbank_protein_id: ID for the protein encoded by the gene
genbank_protein_link: actual link to the protein encoded by the gene
locus_tag: reference to the genetic locus in the organism genome
uniprot_link: link to relevant page on Uniprot
target_organism: organism (i.e. the codon table) for which the part was codon-optimized
description: description of the part's purpose/notable properties
growth_antibotic: selective antibiotic for the gene (in current plasmid backbone)
cloning_method: Method by which to clone the plasmid (as a user)
cloning_enzyme: enzyme with which to clone the plasmid (as a user)
insert_sequence: the sequence for the gene (not including flanking enzyme recognition sites)
copy_number: the copy number for the ori
export_controls: whether or not there are controls on export
attribution: to the author and/or creator of the plasmid part
citations: original publication containing this part (if any)
